<p><strong>1. <a target="_blank"
	href="http://www.feed43.com/">Feed43</a></strong> - My personal favorite, Feed43
is definitely not for the faint of heart. With this service I had the
most control over the final appearance of the feed, but I also had to
take a look at the <a target="_blank"
	href="http://www.feed43.com/tutorial.html">tutorial</a> to get an
understanding of how the syntax works to create variables. If that last
statement was too much for you, then this service probably is too. At
least I got a <a href="http://feed43.com/mgarrett.xml" target="_blank">well-configured
feed</a> from my <a href="http://profy.com/profile/mgarrett/articles/"
	target="_blank">Profy articles page</a> (which is feedless). Others
have used Feed43 to create <a href="http://5thirtyone.com/archives/174"
	target="_blank">RSS feeds of MySpace comments</a>.</p>
