<p><strong>5. <a target="_blank"
	href="http://www.feedyes.com/">FeedYes</a></strong> - Yet another of the easy
feed creation tools, this one requires nothing more than the URL of the
page you wish to transform and a tag. Once the service discovers items
for the feed, it is up to you to weed out the unnecessary ones, by
setting the minimum and maximum number of characters in a title and by
selecting the first and last news items of value. You can try FeedYES
for 14 days for free. You will get access to the full service. If you
like what you see, you can sign up for FeedYes premium, which will let
you create as many feeds as you like. With FeedYES premium, your feed
does not show any advertisments. Great for beginners!</p>
