<p><strong>6. <a target="_blank"
	href="http://www.ponyfish.com/">Ponyfish</a></strong> - I found Ponyfish to be
perhaps the easiest to use. After users provide the URL, the service
provides a small window of that address, where users must simply click
on each link that is to be added to the feed. After this Ponyfish tries
to determine a generic URL with your help (using "*" as wildcard
symbols), in order to retrieve future items to be added to the feed
automatically.</p>
